76561198042009649,Recommended,242760,31139561,Posted: 14 April,all,Lewis2014,"#HonestReviews - For ""The Forest (2014)"". [NO SPOILERS]Overall Rating: 8.6 Excellent!Graphics: 9/10Gameplay: 9/10Audio: 9/10Content: 7/10Multiplayer: 8/10Price: 10/10---------------------------GRAPHICS - 9/10:---------------------------The graphics for this game in my opinion is outstanding for the genre and game type it's specifically refering to. In everygame, there is always room for improvement, but for my understanding I think the graphics on this game are just fantastic. Everything works togethwer well.----------------------------------------------------------GAMEPLAY & PERFORMANCE - 9/10:----------------------------------------------------------The gameplay in this game works really well, it's smooth and fairly optimized, however, I am running 2 GTX 1080s Superclocked, so other's performance may vary. But overall, the performace is fine. The overall gameplay is amazing and has a lot to offer.-------------------AUDIO- 9/10:-------------------The audio in this game likie most games are good. It's just what you'd expect it to be, realistic, and just pure amazingness!--------------------------CONTENT - 7/10:--------------------------For the content of this game I am not as happy with as everything else. The game at this current stage is in Alpha and I expect to see more content released in the near future, however, the game has been in Alpha for quite a while which is disappointing - Like some games that have Alpha for over 4-5 years and release small fixes and patches every few months. This game however as far as I have seen release patches every 2 weeks.The story of this game and end game looks to be unfinished and has been improving since it's early release of the game. I hope to see improvement here too. In my opinion, at this stage it felt a bit 'rushed' to me when I completed the game.It seems that after you've played a few hours of the game that there is not much else to do after building a base and completing the game. Playing Solo can be a bit boring and repetitive as you constantly knock down trees for hours to get the required materials you need in order to complete the things you make.The building in the game is amazing though, simple and easy to use, but you are limited to what you can build as in my opinion again, the lack of items is annoying; it seems like there is not much to build other than a house, walls around it and some light source, of course; you have your decorations etc, but I feel this is a BIG area that needs to be improved.---------------------------------MULTIPLAYER - 9/10:---------------------------------The multiplayer on this game works really well, however, you may experience some bugs and glitches. In addition, there are mods for the game that people can easily abuse and use to ruin games and the fun that people have. The multiplayer works really well and smooth compared to other games like this, I think this game has a great multiplayer setup.The devs have worked hard in fixes loads of issues with multiplayer and single player. But I've ntoiced the differences and I can tell you the game is just getting better and better.Note: At the time of this Review... The devs are currently working on getting dedicated servers for the game which I think will be even better although it's amazing as it is.---------------------PRICE- 10/10:---------------------All I can say is the price is good for what the game has to offer. This may change in the future though.---------------------Overall, you should buy this game if you like Survival Horror Building games. The game seems to be improving rapidly, so expect more fun!Thanks for reading,#HonestReview by Lewis2014.Notes: If you woul like more detailed honest reviews on this or any other games I have, please contact me.---------------------"
,Recommended,242760,25300954,"Posted: 2 September, 2016",all,LittleRage,"I could write a little story about any number of awesome situations this game will throw at you. But I don't feel like it truely explains what you will be buying.Here is what this game offers:Pretty graphics - The game looks awesome,from watching the sunrise because you finally got a break from the night raiding parties to watching the sun disappear knowing things go bump in the night and every moment inbetween is beautiful.Focused crafting - Everything has a purpose or is planned to have a purpose..even the little things like cutting up a cannibal and showcasing him in your yard will upset his buddies.Active devs - I've never seen another EA project match their dedication. On the home menu, it literally has a countdown timer for the upcoming patch. These devs actually give themselves a deadline so they don't lose focus and they use that time to give meaningful updates and minor changes. They listen to their customers. I've seen them add features, tweak features and remove features based on feedback. Your opinion matters here.True horror - Players have put hundreds of hours into the forest, explored every inch of the island, built a fortress and slayed hundreds of cannibals...yet still refuse to leave their base at night or dive deeper into the caves unless they're stuffed with flares and explosives. There is an element of fear in this game that you never really get used to. Things lurk in the shadows, make unnerving sounds, harass you at night, sneak up on you during the day and drag you into the dark when they win.A story - Son gets nabbed, theres a door in a hole. Right now, the story is still in the works and I expect it will be all the way up to release. but, little things are released here and there that really  make you want more.Building - Matched with a horror atmosphere, this is done really well. You build with wood, sticks and stones. You can lay a blueprint for a pre-built structure