76561198148143952,Recommended,242760,28286857,"Posted: 10 December, 2016",all,LAYGO_mi_NAYGRO,"There is this problem, games start in alpha, copy someone else's idea and then they have the nerve to charge you almost 30 bucks to help them make the game suck less then it does, that is if they even plan on getting it out of alpha. Lucky for us, The Forest is none of that crap.I have owned this game since it came out, based on a recommendation of a friend, and I do not regret buying this one. The game looks great for starters. The graphics are somewhere in between a Unity game and a AAA title release. The sounds are fine. No music unless you choose to play it with the in game Walkman so it is very immersive. The fact that your enemy is cannibles and not something worn out like zombies or Russians brings new elements to the game. Tons of options to build and craft. Day/night system as well as weather. There is an ultimate goal, but they are adding the story elements as they go so for now it is mostly a sandbox survival game. The best part has to be playing online with your friends and all the silly stuff that can happen like messing around on the walkie-talkie or stepping on a turtle shell and being launched into the air. They even give you updates as to when the next patch is coming so you feel involved in the development (they even listen to your feedback).TL;DR:Survival crafting game where you fight off cannibles. Still in alpha yet there is high hopes. Tons of fun for single and multiplayer."
