76561198068806335,Recommended,242760,22919300,"Posted: 11 May, 2016",all,frogprincess_q4,"The Forest is still very much in development, so occasionally you will run into some awful bug - recently I was trapped in a cave, for example - but updates are regular and I find the game quite playable even as it is.Disclaimer: I generally play with cheats on - and I love that this is an option! Mostly, I play in Vegan Mode which disables all the cannibals and turns The Forest into a creepy survival game rather than horror survival game. I enjoy exploring the map, building stuff and trying to find enough food and water to live on while avoiding freezing to death. In fact I didn't buy the game until I discovered that it could be played with cheats. However, I do think that there is a lot of the game that I miss out on because of my hypersensitive nerves. There is also Vegetarian Mode which only disables cannibals by day and Ironforest which prevents destruction of your base by cannibals/players.I like that the mutants have their own culture and lives and one day, I swear, I will find the courage to find out more about them. If there was a cheat where I could infiltrate the cannibals and move amongst them without being attacked unless maybe I attacked them first that would just make my day.In the meantime, the map is quite stunning, visually. However, even with the cannibals themselves disabled, the artifacts that they leave around the island can be quite disturbing so I don't recommend to someone who just wants a pretty map and no crawling skin factor.Survival is challenging even without cannibals trying to eat your face. You need to get set up with shelter, fire, food and water pretty quickly. Saving is only possible on a bed (separate from sleeping). If you want to explore you need to make sure that you find a campsite well before dark as you can't carry enough to make a shelter in one go and trying to build at night while freezing and suddenly realising that you can't find any sticks where you are is not so fun. The map is large, but not massive, so after a while you can get bases set up around the map and things are less challenging in that respect.I have never played the multiplayer, but I imagine that it would be a great game to play cooperatively. There are plenty of resources and it's always less scary to have a friend along when mutants are trying to kill and eat you.Somehow, this is one of the game that I play most often, there is just something about it that keeps drawing me back. So, yes, I do recommend it. I only have 40 odd hours on record, so far, but it's one of the few games on my favourites tab, because I know I'll go back there before long even if it's just to see what the developers added in the latest patch.TL;DR It plays well, it looks great and updates are regular. There are cheats. And cannibals."
,Recommended,242760,24597909,"Posted: 29 July, 2016",all,DignifiedPeach,"Summary: Saying that this game is just a 'good early access' game discredits it to a certain extent. This game has so much content that, if released now, would be a very successful game. It's incredibly fun, with the right amount of horror added in. Not only that, but more content is continually being released by the devs and these are some of the most hard working devs I've seen.Pros and Cons:Pros:-Graphics are spectacular; this could be something that people debate, as it's not the graphics of a newer game. however, this game was in fact released in 2014, and it looks crazy good still today.-Animations are very beautiful; trees falling, mutants jumping at you, climbing ropes, all of these feel and look realistic.-Mechanics are nice for the most part. I like the crafting, fishing, and cutting down trees, and the realistic feel they offer. However, I think that the item carrying system could have a little work. You're limited to carrying about 6 rocks at once and 10 sticks, however I think that if they did a weight system, it'd be way easier.-Smart AI. The enemies will know they're losing when you kill 2/3 of their search party, and the third will flee. If you catch a cannibal in a noose trap, their friends can come and release them. if you leave one injured, another will drag them off. They'll send spies to investigate your base, to find weak spots for future attacks. It's really a spectacular thing to witness, expecially in an early access game. Most games I've played have extremely weak/overpoweringly fake AI, but this AI is extremely realistic.-Co-op. This game is incredibly fun with friends.Cons:-Frustrating building setup; this one is probably the number one issue I've experienced. Floors don't snap together, so they just overlay the other floors or get jagged edges. I'd ask the devs to look at ARK: Survival Evolved's building and sorta make it like that.-Small immersion-breaking bugs. Nothing game breaking, as I haven't had my game crash once, but just small things, like chopping down a tree and having a log fly up in the air. Small things like that.-No world consistency (that I've seen); When you get off the game and get back on later, suitcases fill up again, and trees respawn. I don't know if they will add consistency in the future and what that'll do to game optimization, but it's not all that distracting.TL;DR: Fantastic game for an extremely good price, enjoyable with friends, trustable developers.9/10. Dismembering cannibals never sounded better."
