,Recommended,242760,24482083,"Posted: 23 July, 2016",all,Phobos,"Kill a cannibal, chop off his arm, and ♥♥♥♥♥slap his friends all the way to their campsite.I have tried many early access games in my time, and only a few of them are actually worth buying in this stage.The Forestis one of them. It's bizarre, dark, twisted, gory, and haunting. Once you realise the deep trouble you are in, you will not have a moment's chance to relax and take it easy.After a plane crash, your son is abducted by cannibals and you are left nearly dead on the crash site. Your objective is to survive and explore the island to discover where your son is kept and its backstory. That is until you realise you are not alone at all...The game looks beautiful. The island you are in, has forests, lakes, caves and beaches for you to explore. Seems like heaven. Everything is detailed nicelyand you can even observe little birds coming to sit on your hand at times.*DISNEY PRINCESS MODE ENGAGED* You will hear waves crashing on rocks, animals rattling leaves, the song of the birds, and many more sounds appropriate for the landscape. It makes you feel immersed like few games.The survival part is a bit classic, but the crafting system is reimagined in an interesting way. You can carry only a small number of resources, while heavy items like wood logs are better transported to your campsite with sleds. You can craft storage areas for rocks, branches etc that will come in handy later. As for the shelters, you got a plethora of huts and cottages to construct in order to escape from rain (you can even make a treehouse!. Then you got traps, walls, etc. Since there's no minimap (or map in general), an icon pops up in your screen indicating where your unfinished constructions are, so you can always find them. However, it could use some extra freedom with building. But I'm willing to look past that.The enemies are interesting to deal with. At first, they will not hunt you down, they will merely observe you from the shadows and the bushes. Then, they will try to investigate you and your constructions, and then they just might hunt you down by attacking your weakest spots in your defences. If one of them escapes, he will rush back to their camp and call for help to your last known spot. They may scout your base for supplies, organise surprise attacks during the day and set up effigies to warn you to stay away. If you manage to handle them properly though, they will respect you and bow before you, thinking you are some kind of god. They operate in a sophisticated scale which is a refreshing feature in survival games. On the downside, due to the game being a bit unfinished, they act goofy at times, like cramping up in places and not be able to move anywhere or running around without purpose.The real way to play this game, however, iscoop. Get a friend and join forces to conquer The Forest. There's a built-in voice chat feature which makes things easier when you are not in the same room. And that's some really good thinking.Aside some weird bugs, the game is in a really good playable state and the price is ok, but i still suggest to grab it in a sale. It's worth your time, especially if you are a hardened survival veteran.RATING:Gameplay:8/10Presentation:8.5/10Story:7/10Unique Factor: Enemy AI:8.5/10OVERALL:8/10I don't even wanna know whose twisted idea was it to slap cannibals with decapitated limbs."
