,Recommended,242760,10476456,"Posted: 14 June, 2014",all,Barry The Bustin' Bear,"My thoughts on ""The Forest""After making a few videos on it and Clocking some Hours And spending what I had left on it I have a few things to say.Yes you should buy it, you don't need to buy it, but you should. It is perfect for survival junkies and slates the special Itch I've been having for these types of games.The gameplay, though a bit clunky when you encounter a glitch, is still very responsive, and evey swing with your weapon has a very real weight to it. Every encounter with the mutants are usually jarring especially when they sneak up on you, Props to the developers that made it so chopping down a tree can be a tense click session so you can get the supplies and get the hell outa there.The AI is a bit clunky and it gets a bit weird, But when it works it's a good scare when the Tribals come to eat your lovely manflesh.After a Few recordings I truly see how beautiful this game can get and graphically it is lovely, but you might need a beefy Graphics card and processor to run it at max.The blood feature is also a good nod to show that you also need to keep good hygene and keep from getting mucked up with blood can get a wound infected, and the gathering of food is rather nice, Spearing fish and skinning rabbits and lizard to get armor and keeping yourself well fed.The Stealth is rather responsive, hiding behind trees and ducking behind rocks to keep your location unknown you your visitors is good, and I find it interesting that the tribals Will actively watch over their territory, sending patrols out that can locate your camp, and will at times wait in the trees for you to return.The Forest it's self is a enemy to you, you can easily get lost and end up stumbling upon Hungry Tribals, or just loosing your barrings in General.But of course there are some hiccups, at times you can pick up items but they end up deleting out of your inventory, The inventory system could also use a fix so I'm not panicing trying wo switch to my axe when ambushed at the pond.What I want, Coop, and some better tools and weapons, and a Gilly suit would do nice for the stealth.Those and some more building options like Tree houses or Hidden homesBut besides that the game is worth your time, and 15 bucks is a good asking price for this Rather lovely game.So give it a chance and let yourself get lost in this True Survival Horror."
