,Recommended,242760,10337346,"Posted: 3 June, 2014",all,Joelvn,"To start of I'd like to say It's got a recommendation because of the potential this game has.With that I would Like to add that if you are short on cash and looking for a game to play,I would pick up another game. Why? Simply because The Forest is In it's Alpha state, and with thathas a ton of bugs and flaws. It's barely playable in this state. so I would suggest you to buy it in a later state.As for the game itself, not including the bugs,The Forest is a game with lots of potential, and I'm sure the developers will build towards the expectations.The Graphics are great, especially for an indie game. The enemies excist of cannibals, Mutants and wildlife.Crafting in The Forest has been kept simple, and for that I hope there will be improvements, more crafting options and more crafting materials, wich on that part I'm sure will come.What I love about the game is that there are patrols roaming around the island, giving you the feeling your never safe, and always watched. this mechanic is really well done. The cannibals also climb in trees, so you have to be constantly on your toes if you want to survive in this horror survival.The story:The Game starts you off in a plane with your son. unfortunately the plane crashes and you and your son are one of the few survivors of the crash. when you come to your sences you see a man walking up to your son, taking him with him. leaving you falling back to black out again. when you wake up later, wounded and dehydrated in the plane wreck, you start off with some handy supplies such as your backpack, Lighter and a axe found in a stewardesses body. you find out that you have little time to look around the plane wreck and you'll have to start gathering resources and build a shelter to save and rest in, and a fire to stay warm at and cook food.Tips and Tricks:Always be careful picking a location for your shelter since the cannibals patrol the island.If you 'Die' in the game the first time you will be taken to one of the cannibals caves, with them probably assuming you were dead. but beware, if you Die a second time you will really be dead, and you WILL have to start all over again.You are a really buff man, and you can carry 2 logs at a time!There are suitcases lying around the plane wreck and some boat wrecks. they can be opened by hitting them with your axe.Press 'I' to open your inventory, and press 'B' to open up your survival guide.Do NOT let the cannibals flank you. if you encounter a group of cannibals, I would advise you to run and hide. if fighting is inevitable, keep an eye out for all the enemies. they WILL charge at you from behind. If they find your camp and they are attacking you, try to mak them run in the campfire, this way they will be weak enough to take out.BEWARE: some cannibal corpses are known to explode when you hit them.This was my review of The Forest.I would rate it a solid 8/10 when the bugs are fixed, and if they add more features to the game I will reconsider this."
