,Recommended,242760,26189995,"Posted: 23 October, 2016",all,Arteken,"The ForestUPDATE 21.1.2017This game has get pretty big updates since I last played this. Now that the main story is almost complete and more and more features have been added, all I can say is that this game is really, really good. So much to do etc. now. I can still recommend this to every one who likes to build things and explore.As the (lone) survivor of a passenger jet crash, you find yourself in a mysterious forest battling to stay alive against a society of cannibalistic mutants. Build, explore, survive in this terrifying first person survival horror simulator.You are in airplane with random passengers and your son. Plane crashes and creepy cannibal covered in red paint steals your son. Then you start to collect all kinds of things to help you survive. You find some drawings that your son drew. Then you will have to find some tools etc. You can go explore cavesetc. At some point you can go to big cave where your son may be, but this will come in future updates.Game itself:The game has all kind of things to offer. It's pretty easy to learn too. It took like 20 minutes for me to learn all the basic things, but you will learn more and more new things when they add new things to this game in the future.  You have a survival book that has all the basic crafting recepies. Other crafting recepies like bow are easy to learn. You can find all kind of tools and ""guns"" too. You have to gather resouces like chop trees down and collect rocks etc. and then build your own village or almost anything you want.Hunting down animals with weapons is also a thing here. You can find weapons in caves and by crafting them by yourself. You have to eat and drink to stay alive. And like in real life you cant eat rotten meat or poisoned water, so you have to be carefull with those too. There is animals like deers, sharks, tortoises and rabbits. You can also craft armor with things you can get by killing animals and cannibals. There are different kind of cannibals like ""super mutants"" and ""baby mutants"" as I like to call them and they really are scary. Normal cannibals are also pretty scary but not as scary as other mutants. Mutants are also pretty hard to kill. You can get different drops from them when they are killed.Like in real life you have to eat, rest and drink. This game has a bar for health and energy. This also has ""bar"" for hunger and thirstily, so you have to eat and drink to get energy for survival. This also has bar for armor that can be crafted.Playing the game yourself in single player is really scary at first when you have nothing but your basic axe that can be found in the start of the game. You have to start looking for stuff as fast as possible after the crash so you will have enough time to make a shelter for first night of survival. The game will make the cannibals harder night after night for you when you proceed in the game, at least thats how I have seen my single player so far. When playing in single player you will have things to do for a long time. Exploring the caves alone is really scary thing and bit hard at first, but you will spend a lot of time in them trying to find all the special weapons and tools.Playing with friends is really fun. Doing the things this game has to offer with friends is much more fun and more effective. You can make bases and so on so much faster with friends. It's also less scrary when playing with many people.The gameplay works great when playing single player, no lag for me at all. Sometimes when playing multiplayer and if the host has bad internet you can see some lag and missing stuff. I have not seen other problems while playing this. Ofc when this is early access game you will see some little bugs and so on but it's not that bad to be honest.Well to summarise my review this is simple and easy game to play. You can spend hours playing this and you will allways have something to do, at least thats how I see this game. It's not bad at all to spend 15 euros for this. If you like playing sandbox games that include surviving and building things, this is a game for you. My grade for this game is 9/10"
