,Recommended,242760,33509341,Posted: 13 July,all,Hamtaro,"If people were to check my history, I actually do not write reviews but I feel I had to for this game.  Originally when I saw this game, the concept looked pretty good, but overall I wasn't convinced.  I felt like many other games in early access that I had purchased (sometimes upwards of $60), the games were ditched by devs and my money wasted.  I played for a few hours at a friends house but overall it still felt lacking.  So like many others, I simply watched and waited, checking now and then for updates.  Long story short, I kept noticing a series of updates and add ons to the game, and a positive review by majority of the players.  Suddenly it started to catch my attention and after one of my friends got into the game, I decided to give it a go.Boy did they change a lot of things since I lasted played.  Improved mechanics and AI, monsters that were simply decorations in the previous versions are actual things now.  You even have a full storyline you can try to complete in coop or by yourself if you are brave enough.  There are a few things that I still wish the devs pay attention to, which I will mention later, but overall its a well made game and definately worth the current price of $15.  If you're looking for a survival horror (or even just a survival game since you have the option to remove the horror), this game has it for you.Pros:- Sound: The game has amazing sound effects ranging from the rapid foodsteps of an enemy approaching for an attack to their howls and warcries calling for reinforcements or signaling an attack.  When inside caves, there is also many ambient noises such as dripping water, wind and even general rumbling and sounds of things you probably only hear in nightmares.  Overall, excellent job on sound effects, you will be immersed into the environment you are in.- Graphics: I usually dont judge a game by their graphics.  However for those who are concerned, the game is beautiful from all the flora and fauna.  Even if your computer is a potato and you lower all the settings, the game still looks quite beautiful in its own way.  The game does a good job of setting the scenary for you everywhere you travel.- Base Building/Crafting: This is actually very important to me in a survival game.  Gathering resources to staying alive is great but I also enjoy games that give you freedom to do your own things.  There is plenty of that here ranging from building your own house/fort to making things like bows and arrows.  To further increase the fun, they even added traps to the game.  Want to have a large boulder come crashing down into the cannibal face? Go for it.  Feel like luring a group into a ground covered with dried leaves and firing a flame arrow/molotov cocktail into it to roast them all? You got it.  The combinations and tactics that a player can come up with is pretty much amazing.  However, keep in mind that the buildings and walls arn't just there for show.  Unless disabled, enemies can also bash down your walls and rush your base with sheer numbers and strength.- Difficulty: The game does a great job of gradually bringing you into the survival scenario.  It starts off with simply managing your basic needs to just stay alive and scavenging off what you can find.  You'll have some time to explore and try to get an understanding of whats going on.  However, it does eventually start throwing in a few curve balls.  Maybe a curious cannibal wanting to see what you are, eventualy leading to patrols spotting you and seeing who the intruder is.  Next thing you know you're in your base frantically trying to craft weapons/items because there is an angry mob bashing down your walls trying to come in to eat you.  Even a simple daytime work of gathering resources to build your base can quickly turn into a bloodbath.- Enemy AI: So we've played games where the enemy is simply dumb.  Throw an explosive and they keep running towards you ignoring the fact there is something on the ground.  You will not find any of that here as these guys are no joke and do not sit on a thrown explosive item.  The simplist of enemies is more than capable of killing an unarmored freshly spawned player in 2-4 hits.  Careful use of blocking and awareness of the situation is always needed.  These enemies will be fast, dodge and most importantly... flank you from all directions.  Try to attack one and their buddies will hit you from behind and as you turn to keep eyes on one of them, the others will constantly move to throw you off.  You can have all the armors and weapons in this game and all it takes is one well executed ambush to kill you off so don't ever think that just finding something new is all it takes to make the game easy.- Enemy passive behaviors: This is rather unique to this game and I mention this seperately from regular enemy AI.  You'll have to realize that the cannibals on this island have their own behaviors.  There are different tribes, some that even fight and kill amongst themselves.  They do patrols and if they find your base, they can create markings to let their tribes know where you live.  If their scouts spot you, one may fight you while the other flee away to quickly tell their tribes they know of your existence and that you're a threat.  They can also send out hunting parties to track down wherever you are and kill you.  All of these things are usually overlooked and not mentioned but are there in the game.- CoOp Mode: This game is intense and scary in singleplayer but also a lot of fun online.  If you get scared easily, I highly advise playing online with a friend as this definately makes it more enjoyable.  You'll still have your scared moments (especially in dark caves) so don't worry about that, but at least you wont be alone and someone else can watch your back.  Overall, the online portion of the game is really fun and enjoyable.- Active Dev team: For a game which I honestly thought would of been dead long ago, this team has actualy surprised me quite a bit.  They are still around, throwing out updates and adding other great and amazing things to the game.  Even if they were to stop all the updates as of now (07/13/2017), this game is still playable, enjoyable and definately worth the money spent for it.Cons:- I really had to think about it but there is one con that truly bothers me about this game that I hope the Dev looks into (though Im not sure if its even fixable).  Many players enjoy playing survival games in different ways.  Some enjoy doing creative mode and building, others like to give themselves all the weapons/stats upgrades and go on kiling sprees and then others just enjoy playing the game regular for the challenge.  Not many, however, enjoy when you collide all of these together.  One of the biggest flaws of this game is sometimes you could be playing online with a friend, building base and another new player can join your game.  The only difference though is that this player is using mods to give him super running speed, strength and max life/hunger/thirst so he is unkillable.  This kind of thing ruins the online play unless you password the game (which in its own way ruins it for players who want an open game to meet new people to play with).  There really is nothing to help this atm except for kicking players from the game, much like if players joined to simply grief your base.Summary: 10/10Worth the buy? Definately.Have a lot of friends who like Coop survival games? Even better."
