,Recommended,242760,10325541,"Posted: 2 June, 2014",all,Motoagogo,"The Forest is one of those rare gems, a survival game that actually makes you fight to survive. From the moment you leave the plane crash you are being hunted, yet you do not know it yet. As you leave the plane you have a sense of calm, that you are a lone surviver of a massive crash that should have killed you. Congrats, yet now you have crazed mutant cannibals after you and they do not hold back. What is that you just heard in the trees? Probably a bunch of mutants that want to eat your skin for lunch.There are quite a few things to do so far even though the game is in 0.01 Alpha. You can craft shelter, make fire pits, craft traps to protect yourself, and even make an effigy to ward off they mutants after killing them and harvesting their limbs. Only fair right? Also the game is graphically stunning, with tons of animal life to feast on and tons of trees to chop down. Also the caves are stunning and beautiful yet terrifying to go through with just your lighter.Yet at the same time since it is in Alpha there are quite a few bugs. As of this review you cannot save, so make sure you have a full play through and not invest too much time getting a large camp ready. Also there is a dupe bug that will sometimes cause you to spawn a ton of items around you that you have in your hand. Also sometimes the mutants will not stop coming, and have had up to 50 of them attacking me, which was nuts and fun at the same time.My MOTO score:Graphics: 9/10Gameplay 7/10Story: 8/10 (Story is what you make it to be, so please do not fight me on this score. You are a survivor of a plane crash, the rest is up to you.)"
