76561198012359437,Recommended,242760,31406554,Posted: 27 April,all,BORG,"Well, after playing The Forest for some time I think it's time for a review before I forget make one again.The game is pretty well rounded and works well. The are bugs of course as is to be expected with an alpha game, but things are shaping up quite well for this game. Considering the limited resources this group has and the amount of people working on it, it's truly a sight to be seen and you wouldn't believe three to four guys actually made this game in such a short time. The fact that this game does have a direction and great survival elements is really a good selling point for this game. Having a survival co-op experience is nice too.The developers recently created a dedicated server for this game too. It is really nice thing and will allow both co-op and some kind of PvP if people really want to PvP in the PvE world. Who knows ambye they'll make some kind of PvP type system for it eventually with time. I must say too if they make a PvP aspect to this game a reality it will surely be successful since the weaponry is crude. With most survival games being evolved around first person shooter genre and guns, it's a really nice change of pace to throw a spear or swing an axe at things instead of fling bullets. Regardless of whether they ad PvP aspects to the game the PvE is quite fun.The fact that people have already created game modes for this game too is neat. With the Horde mod, you and your friends can challenge waves of enemies to see how long you can survive. It's really quite fun.Another great point about this game is the build system. Since the build system is free-form it's truly fantastic. With little restriction in the building system, you can create virtually anything your heart desires. This especially becomes fun in creative mode which allows you to construct without the hassle of farming wood or stone to build.The storyline is decent. Although the game is nowhere near complete nor the story yet, the fact that there is a storyline that can be put together is great. There is substance to the game.Another great thing about this game is the community really feels nice. Not everyone agrees on everything and some people obviously can be pretty ignorant to others at times,  but in this community it feels less hostile than a lot of other survival genre games. So, if you're looking for a nice community behind a game, this one is pretty decent.All in all The Forest is shaping up to be anice survival experience. I'm sure when it's completed it will still be that way. The developers are responsibe and listen to the community's feedback with an open mind. I can't express how good it feels to know the developers care as much about their community as they do their game and they care about both. It shows in their updates and it shows with how they communicate. This group might be small, but they are professional with their business."
