76561198015176193,Recommended,242760,24722443,"Posted: 5 August, 2016",all,Arnie,"A very mysterious and immersive game that is very different to other bog-standard survival titles out there.Don't boggle about it being an early access game, which normally have bad reputations.It's an adventure which you can either contest alone, or with some friends.It can be scary when you play alone though. Being alone at night in a forest full of cannibals and monstrosities, while hearing disturbing sounds in the distance still sends chills down my spine.Building is one of the most realistic I've seen in games. It requires realistic amounts of materials, for example a woodhouse constisting of 80 logs, really requires 80 logs to build.The survival aspect, as in eating and drinking, is not annoying nor difficult. It just adds to the immersion of the game.The combat is standard, not too clunky but also not very complex. You run to your enemy and swing your axe at them.The missing crosshair while shooting a bow bothered me in the beginning. But I got used to it and probably find it better now not having it there, adding another difficulty in combat.The AI is the interesting part of this game. The cannibals don't act like usual monsters, just running towards you while attacking. They feel like they have their own personality. When they spot you they stand still, looking confused as who you are. They act passive and run around you until they realize what danger you are (or how good your flesh smells). They help their injured allies and always scavange around the island in groups. Their behaviour makes you realize that they are just inhabitants of the island, holding together to protect their property.If you are looking for an unique experience with beautiful and optimized graphics, I definitely recommend The Forest."
