,Recommended,242760,17919718,"Posted: 6 September, 2015",all,Vash(88),"The Forest was one of the first survival games to hit the market a couple years back.  It was released as a single player game, but it now has multiplayer as well; however, the multiplayer lacks some of the features that single player holds.  Though, whether playing alone or with friends, it is an over-all fun game that stands alone from the many other survival titles.  That being said, it has been in ea for a long time now, and the devs often add bugs with updates that require more time to then fix.The survival aspect of the game is a little concerning to me.  It can seem daunting at first, but once you get past the first few days and have a solid base built, it is far too easy to stock up on non-perishable foods and beverages.  The fault comes from the fact that loot re-spawns EVERY DAY...  On top of that, hunting is extremely easy and edible berries re spawn along with the loot.  You can just run up to a deer and hack it to death with an ax if you want meat.The wildlife feel like they belong in the forest with you and there is a solid variety that ranges from crocodiles to rabbits, but like I said already, they are way to easy to kill, and the game animals basically offer themselves to you.The combat is fun at first, but it lacks depth.  There are a surprisingly large amount of melee weapons, but all of them are pointless once you have found the katana.  You are able to upgrade the basic weapons in a way that no other game allows, but again, that is all a moot point once the sword has been found.  There are a number of explosives and a few ranged weapons that are powerful tools, but just like the survival aspect, they are far to easy to acquire.The crafting portion of the game is nothing new.  Though, I do like seeing how much of the forest will be cleared while creating a base.  And I can't think of any other game that you can chop up the dead enemies and either eat them, or turn them into human effigies.The strongest parts of the game are the island and the enemies.The island is large and beautiful.  There are a number of places that can be explored that range from snowy mountains to steamy swamps, even smaller islands that you must build a boat to reach.  Once you have geared up and are feeling brave, the caves are dark and spooky places to explore that hold some of the better loot, as well as some creepy mutants that you will rarely find on the surface.  I had more fun exploring with a friend in this game than in any other.  Hands down.  The openness of the island bioms allow for different play styles to be tested before deciding what works best for you.The aspect of the enemies that makes them such a joy to me is the way they respond to you.  They don't offer any innovative attacks or weaponry, but they will often stalk you when on the surface and even run away and get backup before coming back to kill you later that night.  That type of AI is rarely found in games.  I get tired of enemies that attack without any fear of death, charging at you as  if they have nothing to lose.  The sounds they make at night and the design of some of the large mutants will mess with your mind the first time around as well.Over all, its a great game to play single-player or multiplayer.  With some balancing to the difficulty, this game could shape up to a masterpiece.  In the meantime, I will recommend this game do to its unique in-game content and enjoyable game-play, even if it is a tad easy right now.  The modest price  tag is also a bonus!http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=455604515"
,Recommended,242760,10373865,"Posted: 6 June, 2014",all,Vanta Black,"To me, there has never been anything as intense or rewarding as THE FOREST. It redifines and brings the 'survival horror' genre back in a big way.You begin by crash landing on what appears to be an island covered by a dense forest. You awaken to a few items around you such as food, beer, an axe and other bits of what some would think of as junk. The thing of it is, from the moment of the planes impact, you are being watched and in some cases hunted. After grabbing all you can carry your best bet is to get as far away from the wreck as possible. Corpses of your former fellow passangers litter the land around you and while you may want to stop and admire the scenery (meaning the beautifully rendered foliage and lighting effects) however you MUST run.Chasing you are a band of CANNIBALS. They are great in numbers but are merely studying you at first. You'll see them peering at you from the hill, or from behind a tree. Sometimes one, two, three or even more. Count your blessings and praise the sun for when the night falls, they will be braver.Quickly you make a small fire, then a small shelter out of the trees you have cut down with your axe along with sticks and rocks you find all around the ground. All the while, you're being watched. Then it starts storming. Your fire needs to stay tended to otherwise it will go out and you will surely freeze.Then the sun starts going down and the forest darkens. You hear screams in the distance and footsteps. There are 'warnings' made with the body parts of the airline's unfortunate passangers appearing all over your campsite that you were sure were not there 15 minutes ago.Again, screaming. But this time, its getting closer. Suddenly, you see a light in the distance!! Could it be a rescue?As the light gets closer you see shapes of scantidly clad beings walking twords you. The light is emmited from a bleached human skull one of them is carrying as they search for your exact location. This time, they are here for blood.....I could tell you more, but where is the fun in that? This game is at this moment PRE-ALPHA. There are bugs, glitches and a host of other game breakers. But it never ceases to be fun and exciting. The price in my opinion is worth everything you get in THE FOREST in its current state. It can only get better from here.This is a game of survival, and fortune does not favor you in THE FOREST. You are the prey.Good luck, and hide well."
