,Recommended,242760,24026760,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,Midnight_Medic,"Let me begin by saying my hours in this game are far from accurate. I have spent countless hours playing this game offline.The forest is a game unlike any other on Steam. Some may claim this is not true, and there are other survival games, but in my opinion nothing compares to The Forest.When I first started playing this game the sounds of cannibals in the night would send chills down my spine. The light of a torch can only shine so far, and sometimes the most deadly creatures in the game lie right beyond the torches light, waiting for a chance to pounce. This thought in the back of your head makes you wary of working at night, but sometimes the sacrifice must be made if you wish to prolong your life in single player.The Forest takes many survival factors into consideration giving it one of the most realistic feels of any game on Steam as I said earlier. From sickness, starvation, and dehydration, anything could bring about your death. Cannibals aren't the only thing you must fear.The game is regularly patched, and new content is added with almost every update.Multiplayer is a new beast on its own. Though still focusing on survival the game seems to become both easier, and harder, at the same time. Survival from the elements grows drastically easier, for a time. The cannibals however, grow more frequent and more deadly as the days pass.Cave exploration becomes much easier with friends, and far less dangerous, and with the caves staying cleared thanks to one of the latest patches, the caves can also be used to escape danger if your base ever gets overrun in the later days of survival. (Caves may repopulate after a patch. I experienced this with a group of friends in the pit cave, and we had to flee from the sheer number of enemies that spawned, and our low supply count from the initial exploration).Overall the game is amazing, the gameplay is great, and the time you get to enjoy with friends if you wish is also a plus. I recommend this game to anyone that enjoys a challenge, and prefers their survival simulators more on the realistic side.Pros:+Great Game+Fun with friends+Great Simulator for Survival+Challenging+Interesting, and ever growing story with interesting side discoveries+Frequent Updates+Tree explosions sending logs into your friends heads is always worth a laughCons:-Sharks still stuck on the beach (kinda a plus because we just use the heads and stick them to rocks lol, and if it gets fixed I will update this)-You don't own it yet-Needs more enemy classes (Though it seems more have been added. With the addition of what me and my friends have called the Tubby, (you will be able to tell what I'm talking about if you ever see it, I won't spoil the experience hehehe) I can see many more enemies being added in the future though. So this isn't really a Con, more or less a suggestion that would make the game challenging and force the experienced players to rethink some of their tactics.Buy this game, its worth it. And if you can find it on sale its a steal for the amount of content and fun you will recieve."
