,Recommended,242760,29643933,Posted: 1 February,all,Mister Artorias,"Welcome to my extremely serious review of ""The Forest""The Forest is an early access title that definitely shows promise for its future. Development seems to be active as bug fixes and content updates are being put out quite frequently. The stability of the game isn't very polished yet, but the adventurous nature of the gameplay is what keeps me playing.Forage, fortify, hunt, explore, and... hide? ( The last one was a bit of a joke, unless you're a little scaredy cat such as myself )Survive the onslaught of cannibalistic tribe members! These things will creepily stalk you from the very start of the game. Tensions between the player and the AI savages can increase depending on the player's actions. Will you kill them on sight? Or perhaps simply engage into some friendly political diplomacy? Nawh. Either way, the cannibals will eventually start to breathe down your neck to the point where having a sturdy fort might sound like a good idea. After that concept piledrives itself into that noggin of yours, It's time to get to work! Most of your time spent at the start of the game will most likely be building the base of your dreams. Unless you're an intelligent person that strives for optimization, you'll probably put way too much effort into building a badass fortress ( I'm implying the fact that cutting down trees is all you'll be doing if you don't think small and compact ). After you've made your sweet base, It's time to venture out into the unknown wilderness and explore! Don't mind the nudists off in the horizon that dash from tree to tree, they're simply observant individuals, that's all.Gameplay: Cutting trees / 10Story: Hm? Son is kidnapped by cannibals? I have more important matters to attend to such as spending days on end crafting and refining my masterpiece of a base.Bugs: Quite buggy but not like BUGGY buggy, you know what i'm saying?Overall: Buy it with some friends and you'll have a grand ol' time."
