,Recommended,242760,25161154,"Posted: 26 August, 2016",all,King Pikachu,"The Forest is by no doubt my favorite survial game everIt's not the best optimized and well made game ever, but it more than makes up for it with it's enjoyable gameplay, uniqe setting, great coop experience and insane immersion.Setting/Concept/Gameplay:The Forest is a fresh mix of minecraft styled gathering, base building, survival and cannibals (NOT THE USUAL OVER USED ZOMBIE THING). The game starts out with you the player experiencing a plane crash and then waking up alone as the only survivor. What you decide do after that is more or less up to you!For refrence you can.....Go out and find and explore one of the many cave systems hidden around the forest.Build an comfortable wodden cabin and enjoy the rich wild life.Complete the objectives (theres only a few) note that theres alot more to do than just the list.Pick up the spear and hunt down every single one of those bloddy cannibals.(The developers are adding more things to do every once and then) So don't expect a full story soon---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Sound/Graphics/Immersion:Audio:The sound design is bloody amazing, everything from the sound off rain to the occean sounds realistic.Visuals:The graphics looks extremly good for something early acess, the forest enviorment is just gorgeous (Aside from a few uncommon visual glitches)Immersion:This is in my opinion the best executed part off the game, things takes along time to build,  there's traps, treehouses, boats and alot more to build. You also get this feeling off always being hunted and tracked down by your enemies.---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Technical/Engine/Optimization(Please take this with a grain of salt as im aware off that most off those issues will be fixed before the final release)Performance wise The Forest runs really smooth(60-144 FPS with an gtx 970 and AMD 8350 Stock speed on high settings with 2560x1080p resolution)The big problem here though is the glitches, they are many and often game breaking. Those glitches ranges from falling trough the ground to torches not lighing etc.---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Verdict:The Forest is for sure a potentional gem if they fix the techinal issus aswell as adding more substance to the story/objective off the game :D"
