,Recommended,242760,28692587,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,FuscusNight,"The amount of survival games we've gotten over these past few years is staggering , vast majority of which turned out to be complete utter garbage even after 2 or 3 years of development.The Forest i'd say is one of the few that turned out good over the years and had actually made good meaningful progress, this and the lone dark are probably the  two only survival games of these types I'd recommend checking out.On my first day i pretty much played the game for 11 hours straight with my bf and we couldn't stop, honestly apart from some janky boat/raft physics we experienced, the game almost feels fully finished  yet it still says it's in alpha 0.52, heck the game even has a full on ending now, so it's not just surviving an x amount of days till' yo get bored or die, you do have an objective, one which is rather difficult and will take time to do unless you just  look up youtube guides but  that removes the fun and surprise of exploring the world and its  horrifyingly scary dark a** caves.Probably the bigest reason i'm loving it is because it's a survival game where the enviroment is actually dangerous and f*cking scary as hell to the player, unlike most of these types of games where the enviroment is usually just a minor annoyance while other players are the main thing to fight always, and that's thanks to the game being focused on Co-op/solo play. So yeah no PVP at all, either play solo or co-operate with other players, granted I'd never recommend joining random lobbies, my strong suggestion is to try and get a friend to play it with you but if you can't, rather stick to solo play instead of dealing with strangers online.Visualy the game looks fantastic with some really gorgeous looking lighting effects and foliage that reacts to everything in the world, everytime the wind blows strong and i see and hear the trees leaning and cracking above me it just sends a chill down my spine. It also runs pretty well on my mid-range system that has a now old 760 GTX 2GB, usually sticking around the 40 to 60 fps marks on High visuals quality with pretty much all the bells and whistles [part from SSAO] turned on in a 1080p resolution.One more thing, something i mentioned earlier but want to say it again ; The game is scary as hell during a lot of moments and i love it, this is the first survival game where i genuinly got pi** a** scared due to the excelent atomsphere,sound design and just general unsetling moments it can have as you explore some areas. It pretty much enters full on survival horror and it's bloody fantastick.If you love survival games, you'll love it, if you also love horror, you'll love it even more. This is the 2nd survival game in early acces which I'd say is actually worth your time and money. It's cheaper then vast majority of its competitors that usually cost 20 euros or more and can it drop as low as just 10 euros during sales. This game beats DayZ's,Rust's,Ark's and many others a** in my opinion. I'd also recommend looking into the Long Dark which is the other survival game i mentioned that I'd wholeheartedly recommend checking out."
