76561198077702049,Recommended,242760,10289303,"Posted: 30 May, 2014",all,Carnage,"I'm just going to say that I understand that this is an alpha and an early access game so any negatives I may mention are simply highlights of the main problems that I think should be dealt with sooner rather than later. Its got really good mechanics, it's a very natural and beautiful looking game and has a nice cosy feel to it - it seems to flow quite nicely. It's just I can see it getting a bit repetitive and especially because the likelihood of getting anywhere is slim as the cannibals appear at my base in less than a day (and also whenever I dismember the dead cannibals they tend to explode which killed me midway through my first effigy). Aside from that though it lives up to the hype - it's scary, eerie, and also quite lonely save for the odd turtle or lizard. Also as a side note the rather safe log cabin assembles itself in mid air (not sure if it moves to the ground when finished because I haven't been able to accumulate 82 logs yet). It is a game that would be worth playing at night as it would create a great atmosphere as well as the fact that it might be easier to see things as the in-game brightness can make this quite difficutlt (logical when you're in a cave I know but it does tend to take away the inquisitive nature of the game if you have to study something meticulously up close with a very weak lighter just to see what it actually is). The cannibals themselves though I expected to sort of become more brave and dangerous as the game progressed which i'm sure is the aim in the next few patches, but at present they attack straight away and the fact that they spawned at my base on multiple occasions whilst I was out collecting logs also made it very difficult for me to progress as I couldn't then access my gear. Overall I would say that a few tweaks of the above mentioned issues would make the game worthy of a fuller release were they tackled correctly and with the few developers there are it is a momentous achievement to have produced such an immersive experience so far - I can't wait for what's to come! Keep it up :)"
