,Recommended,242760,18082214,"Posted: 18 September, 2015",all,B.A.D. ~Vegan w/a shotgun,"Ever since it's first early alpha release I have been obsessed with this game. The visuals and stunning the developers went above and beyond to create a living breathing forest atmosphere for players to explore. With simulated weather, altitites, wild life etc the game really immerses players into the island world.As a survival horror, this game takes player surival and believability seriously one of the most realistic survival games I've ever played. Players will be required to keep tabs on their hunger, temperature, thirst levels and infections to survive after their plane has crashed landed. Clean drinking water becomes the upmost importance for players as thirst is constantly going down, and most streams/ponds are poisoned.The game has an amazing crafting system and surivival book for notes and tips on how players can survive and what crafting options they have. Most people have likely already seen videos of the tree cutting, but guys, guys! YOU ACTUALLY CUT DOWN THE TREES. You fell them, with your tools and they fall. Brilliant. Seriously guys we've been gathering pixelated resources for years and trees have never actually fallen.Go buy this game! DO IT! Story mode is coming, but for now multiplayer survival horror is brilliant. If you aren't a fan of survival games, then maybe this isn't the game for you. You are literally stranded on an island so you spend a lot of time in nature trying not to die, which is challenging and rewarding but I can see how some people in this COD erra want more'action'. There is combat and enemies in this game, but for most players the best strategie to to run, avoid, hide and build until you have a secure location to wage war."
