76561198053914627,Recommended,242760,10850707,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,щит,"This is a very interesing game to play, it differs from most survival games, because of your intuition. In other games you think, yeah I'll find a gun if there are zombies, shoot them in the head, it's fine, I won't get cornered and I'll be okay. In the forest,right from the start you can tell it's different.You see the inhabitants, (I refuse to call them mutant's, you're the weird one here) they aren't random, they don't meander about aimlessly like other enemies on survival games, they know you're there. They watch, document and find you quite perplexing. You cut down trees to build a small hut, you are shocked to find yourself without other humans, you rummage through suitcases in search of equipment, most importantly, you look like a foreign delicacy.It becomes obvious they want to eat you, they have patrols that moniter how you disturb the environment, they notice the felled trees, the little constructions you make. Every time you go to cut a tree, you can't help but feel you're being watched. You start to be more selective of the places you look for resources, you try to always have a good vantage point, YOU want to watch THEM, they make you uncomfortable, why do they walk around with clubs? Where are they getting these strange body like clothing accessories? Then you realise... Over the last night, an effigy was erected, it had two human heads on a short stick, you recognise one of them as an air hostess who had serverd you coffee... it all makes sense, the lack of survivers and more importantly, the lack of bodies.You Become more fevered, you start to build weapons, walls, traps, anything to keep these people at bay. But it seems, the more you do, the more interested they become, the number of patrols increase (or are you just imagining it?) some patrols become violent, you try and fight them back, but three on one isn't fair, they keep trying to surround you, but you remember the molotov you made, fumbling around in your backpack, you finally pull out the small bottle of booze and light it up. Darting through a hole in thier formation, you drop the molotov at your feet, only to see them chase right after you. You were lucky, they all caught and are no more than burnt corpses.Who want's to leave a bunch of corpses on their metaphorical front lawn? Not you, so you cut them up and throw together your own effigy and add it to your bases defenses, you hope it will scare them, they seem to have enough brain power to understand that it's their mates head pinned to a spike. You head back to work making your base self sustainable and everything starts to go the way you expected your journey to go, build a nice defensive house and fight some enemies and that's how it goes... right?The games itself is alpha release, for an alpha, very few game breaking bugs, which is more than can be said about some alpha releases. There are a few clipping issues for some of the textures, I came across a bug which deletes half of your inventory when loading it up for a second time and it stops me from picking up fish and alcohol, which, though irritating, doesn't stop me from playing the game, it just means I learnt how to fight with an axe. The game is definitly not for common consumption, if you want to make more gran structures I suggest you play something like minecraft or 7 days to die, but if you want to live in constant fear, constant struggle and constant thrill, definitly worth a pickup, for a bang up job on a stable and functioning alpha release, with hopefully plenty of content to come."
76561198035021601,Recommended,242760,10361982,"Posted: 5 June, 2014",all,Freric,"A very good, yet buggy game.It shows a lot of promise, but is already fun after the last patch.Some advice: fire is your best friend, from a distance.  Build any fires some distance from your camp, as they can be easily seen and attract attention.  Craft combine cloths and alcohol to make molitovs.  It is the only weapon that even gives you a chance against groups larger than 2.  The flare gun is the only ranged weapon.  It can be found in the cockpit of the crashed plane, which is randomly placed meaning you have to search for it.  You can also find the flare gun in the cave where you wake up if they nock you out instead of killing you.  There you will also find the first two-handed rusty axe.  this lets you block with the right mouse button.  The islanders will do simple attacks at first, but like AI-war will learn what you are doing, and slowly add in better tactics.  I died because they tricked me into backing up into a spike trap.  Also of note, after i defended my camp, they built several effigies around it while i was asleep to tell me to go away.  Eventually, they even built a temporary camp near mine as a strike base.  A must: build a small side camp away from your own.  If your manin camp is ovverun, you need somewhere to go.Good luck."
