,Recommended,242760,10331419,"Posted: 2 June, 2014",all,dandoozled,"The Forest is a terrifyingly awesome game! Once you get ingame you are left alone after a horrific plane crash, where apparently know one survived but you. You are a lone survivor and have to build your own shelter hunt and find food to fill up your belly, but the world is in't a trip in lala land; you will run into inhumane enemies. You will run into these creatures that look very similar to humans, but they aare much stronger and faster than you. They are challenging, especially if you find yourself surrounded by more than one. The best way to survive these cannibals is by running away or fleeing. If you get killed by the cannibals they will abduct you, and take you to a cave where you will find the rest of the airplane passengers. This cavern is very big, and will have to be explored later on in the game, but I would stay away from it for the first few days. In this cavern you will have to escae, but if you get lost you might find yourself in a very dangerous situation. Deeper in the cavern live these mutations, some look like people wrapped around by human skin. These mutated creatures are probably the most dangerous, and they will be quick to kill you. Ofcourse they live in the caves! So if you don't go in there you'll be safe right? WRONG! After a couple of days when you have developed your little safe haven, and you think nothing can get you... they will emerge from the depths of the cave and will surround your home then they will break through anything they need too; just to kill you. This is a very challenging game, and I HIGHLY RECOMMEND getting it if you are into open world survival games like Rust, or are into horror games; trust me the cannibals do a good job at sneaking up behind you, then SCARING THE LIVING♥♥♥♥♥♥OUT OF YOU!!! This game is fun, but it does have a lot of bugs and glitches; it's fine because it is in Alpha and hopefully they will fix it soon - SlenderCat"
