76561198049568708,Recommended,242760,16104844,"Posted: 31 May, 2015",all,Rad Shiba,"The Forest is a brilliant game. Both the concept, graphics, atmosphere, and the gameplay are all great. Early access or not, this a game worth picking up.Pros: well to start out, it looks beautiful. The island looks great, both thanks to the graphics and the layout of the island itself. The way the light goes through the trees has made me stop actually playing and just look at it many times. While obviously not what you buy the game for, this is something worth mentioning. On top of this, the world feels alive. It's hard to explain but the island really feels like a real forest (or at least as close as a game can come to feeling real). The combat feels good, as the weapons feel like they have weight and power. Also, of course the survival part of the game is great and is the strongest part of the game. You have to manage food and water intake and must build to protect yourself from the outside world. It can be truly nerve wracking to be stuck in your fort for the night knowing you're out of food. The building aspect is also pretty cool. It's really exciting when you're building your walls and you need just a couple more pieces of wood to complete it, but the sun has gone down so you have to finish before cannibals show up.Cons: well, the biggest problem is that it's early access. Many may claim that I can't list this as a problem since it is marketed as early access and never pretends to be anything but early access, but the truth is that it is a product and when you buy it this is what it'll be like (at least for now). The game is often a buggy mess. The ""zombies"" will glitch through walls often times. You'll use resources making something just to have it not actually be crafted. These kind of glitches aren't too common, but they can kill you when they do happen and ruin your 5 hour game. While I'm sure in 6 months they'll fix the problems, but for now they exist and that what you have to play with. The other problem is kind of a half problem half not. The game's weapons are too weak. Like I said, they feel powerful but they really aren't. While I don't mind weak weapons in a game like this, they're too weak in my opinion. Even when you're 10 hours into a game and have a super fort, if you get caught fighting even 4 or 5 enemies, you're life is in serious danger. I love having the game make you feel as if you're truly outgunned so to speak, but here it feels like you're using a foam sword to fight a tank. However, many people will love how the game makes you avoid combat often because of this so it's a personal preference really.In conclusion, this a game that is good as it is, but I feel will only truly reach its full potential in a couple of months. I recommend buying it now, as it is still REALLY fun and of course the more money the studio has, the better they can make their game. I'd give it a 7.5/10 as of now and expect it to be around a 9/10 when it's finished"
