,Recommended,242760,24027439,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,JoeLudicrous,"*( I'm aware this is early access and subject to change, This review will update as the game does to inform the potential buyer what to expect if they purchase right now) *-A crashed commercial plane leads to a Forest survival game with a twist.Cannibals roam the island (some mutated) making for a daring task to explore the massive map which includes an entire under ground cave system where you can discover new places, secrets, hidden items, new tools, weapons and consumables.-PROS-8 Player Co-Op with the ability to host the servers and save the game in many areas around the map.( super fun the more friends you have)Massive Map, this is a beautiful world that with occupy you time and satisfy your eyes with wonderful visuals.The inventory system is done very well. You have a backpack that only has limits to the amount of specific items you can carry like sticks or rocks, meds drinks snacks but doesn't limit some other things like sap and leafs. TY for no weight limits :)Plenty of items to put into that inventory, And more coming. No shortage of consumable or usable content.Ever expanding crafting systems with tools and items. Create variants of all your items or create new ones with new combinations coming out seemingly every update.A semi advanced system for crafting structures you can build for shelter or eye candy. Simple to use as well.A Nicely done Survival Guide that will generally have what you need to know in most situations like crafting and general knowledge of the the things you can come across on the open world.The game seems to run smooth almost always while looking fantastic even when playing online. ( FX 8350, Radeon 7970 16GB Ram) Full List of Graphical Options from Post processing effects like DoF, Motion Blur, Bloom, AF, etc. And a wide variety of texture and terrain settings.Fully Open World. If You can see it. You can almost always reach it.( Provided you have necessary tools and resources.There is life other than the cannibals, there are numerous animals such as Turtles, Lizards, Sharks, Dear, Alligator, Rabbit Squirrel,Various Birds, Fish and a few more.Some animals attack like The Sharks and Crocs, Some don't harm like deer, rabbit, lizards etc. Both you can hunt and eat.There are some decorative and non beneficial animals like Spiders under rocks and Bats in caves, flies over dead bodies and Starfish in the waters.The devs are SOLID. they have large updates every cycle and inform you with a counter in the main menu when the next one rolls around. They also tell you Everything they tweaked in patch notes. You can count on support with this one. I think your money is safe on this Early Access.CONS-(Some here are MY Personal Preference and some are more suggestions than Cons, Which many of friends have agreed with. Subject to disagreement if you'd like, but Its My Review :)There is no character customization, you cannot choose what you wanna look like or even what you wear when you spawn or when you progress into the game, kinda lack luster compared to other smaller survival games that offer this feature. ( Not counting the armor you can apply with Bone or Lizards skin that provides a visual add on.I believe the full day should last longer,the full day rotates in less than 25 minuets and that is seemingly too quick for a game that offers great realism and immersion. Longer days with allow you to work more without getting hungry soon after you just ate making it easier for beginners to get a grasp and explorers to explore. Longer nights means greater level of danger and risk, If you know night is gonna last a long time then you will think twice once the sun starts to set about straying too far from your base. And increasing intensity and level of fear if you do. I really believe this would make the immersion level greater.Stealth System would be a Great AdditionI notice there is no way around the cannibals. They always seem to know where you are and you really cant avoid them.in caves and dark forest, I crouch to sneak past but it fails every time. So you only have 1 linear option of going about and that is fighting or trying to run. Part of surviving is being knowledgeable about your environment and surroundings. But as of now you can only out muscle the cannibals. They are faster, hit hard and they outnumber you too. Grrr. No fair.There is No ambient music.Now don't get me wrong, the sound in this game is Very well done. And only gets better via updates. But the lack of ambient music when just strolling through the forest, sitting around a campfire or navigating through the caves can make the game feel somewhat boring at times. Subtle Ambient music like those found in Skyrim or Witcher 3 ( Just examples, Not comparing) would Really lighten things up.No way to pause the game.Hey when you playing a video game with or without friends. There are time in which we have to afk, we are people. A pause feature would be nice. taking a s*** and returning to death isn't cool.Regenerating Health.Besides Meds, (Which should have more than 8 Max in inventory) In order to regenerate health. You have to have have a full stomach and be free of thirst and....overindulge to gain more Health???  An option to be able to craft bandages fo wounds would be more realistic and sense full. Especially when Cannibals hurt bad, fire burns nicely and poison from berries doesn't help.Interior Decor for the ''Home'' you build would be coolHave a big house that took ages to make, but is extremely empty and has only one bed for multiple people XD.Excellent game all in all. Recommended for sure. Buy it for your friends, its cheap and has bewbs if your into mutant bewbs :)Given its early access and devs are great. 9/10 with ALOT of potential. Buy it Now!"
