76561198009619002,Recommended,242760,10348342,"Posted: 4 June, 2014",all,TheFishMan,"The Forest is currently the latest survival/horror game on the gaming market. I've personally been playing it for quite a few days now. The following is my review/guide/conclusion:The game is undoubtedly in a pre-alpha stage as the developers will state when you launch the game. There're quite a few bugs, though nothing which is game ruining. The game basically starts with you taking part in a horrific plane crash. You get knocked unconscious and when you wake up your son gets ""abducted"" by one the island's many inhabitants. And yes, you're not alone in this horror game. There're lots of foes for you to battle. The hostile inhabitants, who roam the island, are cannibalistic mutated humans who basically seek to inflict you harm. In order to survive you must keep yourself warm and dry plus keep yourself satiated. And thus the exhausting battle for your survival begins.When you first encounter the cannibals DO NOT get cocky and charge. Most commonly and regularly they're just scouting. If you do get too close you might end up getting assaulted with full force. To avoid this particular matter you ought to run off.The graphics are quite stunning actually and they greatly enhance the surrounding environment. Unfortunately the game is poorly optimized at this particular point and hence your system may have a difficult time running the game in ultra settings. I've got a brand new GTX Titan Black which I've overclocked. Additionally I've an overclocked i7-4770k. Sometimes my FPS drops down to 30 or lower despite the fact that I've got an expensive high end system.The game obviously has got quite the potential to become a marvellous game. This is an indie game and has got a long way to go before it's finished. I know that the developers are currently updating and patching as fast as they possibly can.As a conclusion I would definitely  recommend The Forest to everyone who's fond of survival and/or horror games. Both of these genres are very much present in this particular game.I highly hope this pushed you in the direction of purchasing the game :)"
