,Recommended,242760,13047142,"Posted: 22 November, 2014",all,Trazza,"THE FOREST REVIEW:Isnt it a scary moment when your lighter goes out in the dark caves of ''the forest'' when you hjear nearby footsteps that haunt you. The forest is yet another survival game that has been released on the store. You might think it is a zombie horror game but it isnt, your fighting against cannibles. Now first thing i need to adress is the graphics, they are amazing. from the lush foliage to the sunrays that connect with the tree's, it is imaculate. The forest encourages exploration and hunting to find food, it also encourages you to build your first shelter fro the night along with a fire to warm you up. The forerst stretches the survival genre as it adds new methods that i have never seen like actually hunting fish with a spear and  having to always be alert for enemies, it truly is the one emersive game. The forest is in alpha, so expect glitches along your journey. The forest has recently added in a new coop experience which allows you to survive the night with friends. Overall, the forest is a great game but it has glitches which i can forgive as it is inn alpha. 8.7/10"
